title: Conquering Florida: Airboating in Kissimmee
text:
Updated: 12:17 p.m. Thursday, July 23, 2015 | Posted: 6:51 a.m. Thursday, July 23, 2015 Conquering Florida: Airboating in Kissimmee In Partnership with VisitFlorida.com 
Known for his greatness in motocross, Florida native Ricky Carmichael retires his bike for the day to conquer Florida by airboat with Captain Steve's Swamp Buggy Adventures . Captain Steve, a fifth generation Gladesman, personally teaches Ricky the ins and outs of what an airboat safari can entail in the alligator swamps. Ricky tests the water with some old racing tricks to see what the airboat is truly made of, surprising even Captain Steve. Without a doubt, Ricky proves Florida can meet the need for speed and adventure.
